### Description

Using the STJ source generator to generate the `JsonTypeInfo` for types yields incorrect results when using the `JsonTypeInfo` in a HTTP request if the properties of the type are source generated.

### Reproduction Steps

My Web API:
```csharp
var app = WebApplication.Create(args);
app.MapGet("/person", () => Results.Ok(new Person("Steve", 50)));
app.Run();

record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

My Console Application:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using System.Text.Json;
using System.Text.Json.Serialization;
using Lombok.NET;

namespace Test;

public class Program
{
    private static readonly HttpClient HttpClient = new();
	
    public static async Task Main()
    {
        var options = new JsonSerializerOptions(JsonSerializerDefaults.Web);
        options.AddContext<JsonContext>();
		
        var person = await HttpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<Person>("http://localhost:5000/person", options);
        Console.WriteLine(person.Name);
    }
}

partial class Person
{
    [Property]
    private string _name = default!;

    [Property]
    private int _age;
}

[JsonSerializable(typeof(Person))]
partial class JsonContext : JsonSerializerContext
{
}
```

I use [Lombok.NET](https://www.nuget.org/packages/Lombok.NET/) to generate the properties from my fields.

### Expected behavior

The Console Application prints "Steve".

### Actual behavior

Th Console Application prints nothing since `person.Name` is null.

### Regression?

_No response_

### Known Workarounds

When defining my `Person` class like this, everything works:
```csharp
class Person
{
    private string _name = default!;
    private int _age;

    public string Name { get => _name; set => _name = value; }

    public int Age { get => _age; set => _age = value; }
}
```

This is however exactly what Lombok.NET generates.


### Configuration

.NET 7.0.0-preview.6
macOS 12.5.1 with Apple Silicon

### Other information

I have a hunch that this is caused by the fact that source generators cannot be dependent on each other and the STJ generator runs before the property generator. However I can see that the STJ generator generates a `JsonTypeInfo` for `Int32` and `String`, so it seems to find the properties somehow.

