Yes we could provide an opt-in mechanism to include the path (i.e `JsonException.Path`) produced by the serializer or an API to for users to set it.

@steveharter mentioned that the thought during API review was that the user may have a specific error message already and might not want the exception info cluttered.

Depending on user feedback here we might want to challenge that assumption and perhaps include path info by default.

