The short form answer to your question is "specific types, but really up to the developer writing the ReferenceResolver to determine." The rest below is just context :D

For the use case prompting this, I have created an Attribute to be used on the key property of any class that is to be referenced - and a custom ReferenceResolver, which then returns an id value of "propertyName: value", resulting in `"$id": "propertyName: value"` in the JSON. This makes some sense in our particular business environment.

For example, a Person might have a number of Contracts, each of which have an ContractId, and one of which is the Primary Contract:
```
{
  "personId": 123,
  "contracts": [
    {
      "$id": "contractId: 1",
      "contractId:" 1,
      "department": "bla bla",
...
    },{
      "$id": "contractId: 2",
      "contractId": 2,
...
    }
  ],
  "primaryContract": {
    "$ref": "contractId: 2",
```

Here, I would use my ReferenceKeyAttribute on the ContractId property of the Contract class, indicating that reference IDs should be generated for these objects.

