### Background and motivation

Polymorphic JSON using a boolean discriminator cannot currently be de/serialized, for example:
```ts
// TypeScript definition
type Content =
    | { isRich: false, text: string }
    | { isRich: true, text: RichText }
```

### API Proposal

```csharp
namespace System.Text.Json.Serialization.Metadata
{
    public readonly struct JsonDerivedType
    {
        public JsonDerivedType(Type derivedType, bool typeDiscriminator);
    }
}
```

### API Usage

```csharp
[JsonPolymorphic(TypeDiscriminatorPropertyName = "isRich")]
[JsonDerivedType(typeof(PlainTextContent), typeDiscriminator: false)]
[JsonDerivedType(typeof(RichTextContent), typeDiscriminator: true)]
abstract record Content;

record PlainTextContent(string Text) : Content;

record RichTextContent(RichText Text) : Content;
```

